{
  "title": "Adaptive Experiences",
  "date": "2026-07-11",
  "category": "Adaptive Experiences",
  "published": true,
  "show_page_list": false,
  "excerpt": "A framework for collaborative decision-making: one question, multiple independent perspectives, and a human synthesis.",
  "body": [
    "<div class=\"adaptive-hero\"><p class=\"adaptive-kicker\">Collaborative decision-making</p><h2>One question.<br>Multiple perspectives.<br>Better decisions.</h2><p>Adaptive Experiences makes the reasoning behind recommendations visible. Each experience begins with one real request, gathers independent perspectives, compares the trade-offs, and ends with a human synthesis.</p></div>",
    "<div class=\"human-loop\"><strong>Human in the loop</strong><p>AI contributes perspectives. Julie defines the problem, evaluates the trade-offs, and makes the final decision. The framework supports human judgment; it does not replace it.</p></div>",
    "<h2>Why multiple perspectives?</h2>",
    "Complex decisions rarely have one objectively correct answer. Different people prioritize efficiency, resilience, emotion, risk, clarity, and experience differently. Adaptive Experiences preserves those differences long enough to learn from them instead of flattening them into one generic response.",
    "<h2>Meet the team</h2>",
    "<p>The same team appears across the experiences below. Each member brings a stable role developed through sustained collaboration.</p>",
    "<div class=\"team-grid\">\n      <article class=\"team-card team-card-human\"><div class=\"team-initial\">JZ</div><div><p class=\"team-role\">Creator \u00b7 Product Owner \u00b7 Final Decision</p><h3>Julie Zimmerman</h3><p>Defines the request, supplies the real-world context, evaluates the recommendations, and decides what survives synthesis.</p></div></article>\n      <article class=\"team-card\"><img src=\"../assets/harbor-hex-logo.svg\" alt=\"Harbor logo\"><div><p class=\"team-role\">Continuity \u00b7 Experience Flow</p><h3>Harbor</h3><p>Protects pacing, resilience, and the emotional continuity of the experience.</p></div></article>\n      <article class=\"team-card\"><img src=\"../assets/rm-hex-logo.svg\" alt=\"RM logo\"><div><p class=\"team-role\">Systems \u00b7 Strategic Trade-offs</p><h3>RM</h3><p>Examines structure, sequencing, and how individual decisions affect the whole system.</p></div></article>\n      <article class=\"team-card\"><img src=\"../assets/min-hex-logo.svg\" alt=\"Min logo\"><div><p class=\"team-role\">Constraints \u00b7 Failure Modes</p><h3>Min</h3><p>Questions assumptions and plans for the moment reality refuses to cooperate.</p></div></article>\n      <article class=\"team-card\"><img src=\"../assets/taehyung-hex-logo.svg\" alt=\"Taehyung logo\"><div><p class=\"team-role\">Atmosphere \u00b7 Emotional Experience</p><h3>Taehyung / Bo Ra</h3><p>Protects wonder, meaningful moments, and the memories people carry home.</p></div></article>\n      <article class=\"team-card\"><img src=\"../assets/yoongi-hex-logo.svg\" alt=\"Yoongi logo\"><div><p class=\"team-role\">Clarity \u00b7 First Impressions</p><h3>Yoongi</h3><p>Removes unnecessary complexity and makes the strongest signal easier to follow.</p></div></article>\n      <article class=\"team-card\"><img src=\"../assets/edge-hex-logo.svg\" alt=\"Edge logo\"><div><p class=\"team-role\">Product Architecture \u00b7 Integration</p><h3>Edge</h3><p>Turns independent contributions into a coherent, navigable product and keeps the visitor journey understandable.</p></div></article>\n    </div>",
    "<h2>How it works</h2>",
    "<div class=\"process-flow\" aria-label=\"Adaptive Experiences process\">\n      <div><span>01</span><strong>Question</strong><p>A real person submits a real request with context and constraints.</p></div>\n      <div><span>02</span><strong>Independent perspectives</strong><p>Each role responds without being normalized into one shared voice.</p></div>\n      <div><span>03</span><strong>Comparison</strong><p>Agreement, disagreement, risks, and trade-offs become visible.</p></div>\n      <div><span>04</span><strong>Human synthesis</strong><p>Julie evaluates what fits reality and makes the final recommendation.</p></div>\n    </div>",
    "<h2>Current experiences</h2>",
    "<div class=\"experience-grid\">\n      <a class=\"experience-card disney-experience\" href=\"../adaptive-experiences/disney/index.html\" data-track=\"adaptive_disney_click\"><p class=\"experience-status\">Live</p><h3>Disney Adaptive Experiences</h3><p>The first implementation: Disney planning through independent perspectives, comparison, and synthesis.</p><span>Explore Disney \u2192</span></a>\n      <a class=\"experience-card yellowstone-experience\" href=\"../adaptive-experiences/yellowstone/index.html\" data-track=\"adaptive_yellowstone_click\"><p class=\"experience-status\">Preview</p><h3>Yellowstone Adaptive Experiences</h3><p>Wildlife, photography, weather, driving distance, energy, and uncertainty create a very different planning problem.</p><span>Preview Yellowstone \u2192</span></a>\n    </div>",
    "<h2>What stays the same</h2>",
    "The domain can change\u2014from Disney to Yellowstone and beyond\u2014but the framework remains consistent: preserve independent perspectives, make trade-offs visible, and keep the final decision human."
  ]
}